Name: # of hauls
Description: number (quantity) of hauls, the result of an effort to obtain, collect something

Name: # of hooks
Description: number (quantity) of hooks, a piece of metal or other material, curved or bent back at an angle, for catching hold of or hanging things on.

Name: # of net sweeps
Description: number (quantity) of sweeps, sturdy nets often with a canvas bag, that are used to collect insects and other invertebrates from long grass.

Name: # of nets
Description: number (quantity) of nets,a length of open-meshed material made of twine, cord, rope, or something similar, used typically for catching fish or other animals.

Name: # of passes
Description: number (quantity) of passes, a single complete cycle of operations.

Name: # of traps
Description: number (quantity) of traps, a contrivance used for catching game or other animals, as a mechanical device that springs shut suddenly.
